        output='Based on the provided S-1 Preamble text, the AI segment’s customer base is highly diversified and spans the entire AI value chain. It ranges from a massive global consumer audience on the X and Grok platforms to enterprise and government entities utilizing tailored AI solutions, as well as third-party organizations leveraging the company\'s gigawatt-scale compute infrastructure. \n\nHere is the detailed breakdown of the AI segment\'s customer base:\n\n### 1. X Platform Users and Consumer Subscribers\nThe foundation of the AI segment\'s consumer ecosystem lies in the integrated X and Grok platforms, which serve as a massive funnel for user engagement, data generation, and paid subscriptions:\n*   **Broad User Base (MAUs):** As of March 31, 2026, the integrated platforms had over **1.3 billion supported accounts** active in the trailing twelve months, including approximately **550 million Monthly Active Users (MAUs)**. These users generate approximately 350 million daily posts, providing the real-time data stream that gives Grok its competitive, truth-seeking advantage.\n*   **Grok AI Users:** Out of the total MAUs, approximately **117 million MAUs** actively engaged with Grok’s AI features.\n*   **Paid Subscribers:** The company is actively converting free users into paying customers, reaching approximately **6.3 million active paid subscribers**. This base is split between:\n    *   ~4.4 million X Premium and Premium+ subscribers.\n    *   ~1.9 million Grok subscribers across tiered offerings (SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, SuperGrok Lite, and basic), which unlock advanced reasoning models, multimodal capabilities (like Grok Imagine and Grok Voice), and priority compute.\n*   **Advertising Customers (Enterprises):** While consumers use the platform, **advertisers** are a vital B2B customer base that monetizes this user activity. Enterprises leverage X’s scale and Grok’s AI-driven performance marketing tools to run high-impact, contextually relevant ad campaigns that feel integrated into real-time public conversations.\n\n### 2. Enterprise and Government AI Customers\nThe company is aggressively expanding its B2B and B2G (Business-to-Government) footprint by offering secure, tailored AI deployments and API access to organizations:\n*   **Enterprise Customers:** Businesses are served through products like **Grok Business, Grok Enterprise, and the Grok API**. These offerings provide customized deployments tailored to specific enterprise workflows and strict security needs. They are sold on flexible **license-, consumption-, or outcome-based pricing models**. \n    *   *Use Cases:* Enterprises use these tools for coding, product development, and management. The company is also developing **Macrohard** (an agentic AI platform built with Tesla) designed to fully emulate digital workflows and automate entire business processes. Furthermore, the company is partnering with developer platforms like *Cursor* to create jointly-owned coding and knowledge-work AI models.\n*   **Government Customers:** Leveraging its existing track record and structural advantages as a large government contractor (e.g., via Starshield in the Space/Connectivity segments), the AI segment targets public sector agencies through specialized products like **xAI Gov**. The company views governments as significant future consumers of AI applications for national security and operational efficiency.\n\n### 3. Computational Infrastructure Customers\nBeyond software, models, and applications, the AI segment monetizes its massive physical hardware and power infrastructure:\n*   **Third-Party Compute Customers:** The company has established a dual advantage in cost efficiency and deployment speed by building gigawatt-scale AI training clusters (COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II). Recognizing that vast, power-efficient computational resources are a critical bottleneck for the broader AI industry, the company **offers its compute infrastructure to third-party customers